title: Grateful Dead Live at Knickerbocker Arena on 1993-03-27
description: Hell In A Bucket, Bertha, The Same Thing, Peggy-O, Queen Jane Approximately, Broken Arrow, Loose Lucy, Cassidy, Casey Jones Eyes Of The World-> Estimated Prophet-> Comes A Time-> Corinna-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel, All Along The Watchtower, The Days Between, One More Saturday Night, E: I Fought The Law

reviews.review_text:
Good Fun A couple of firsts for me in this show (casey jones and comes a time, which i thought was high time during the first few notes) so i may love it just for that.  however, i remember the playing to be solid throughout and just one of the better shows of the year.  

sound is right on as it is with all of these SBD's being uploaded (thank you thank you thank you).  enjoy!
HOT great  show boys are right on key w/this hot jerry sounds good        this is a keeper for sure   hiltzyy.........

? the last good show i saw
This fileset sounds as good as it can
check it out if only for the comes a time
thank you each and every one of you all of us who made this possible
i love you all 
not faade away
and the SBD is just so crispy even corrina sounds good

clipping come on dudes!!  listen close to days between...that is not a high hat, it is digi noise man....when i read a 5 star review and hear clips, it makes me sad.......good performance, bad clips......3
This was my beginning. Great show, great memories, good recording.  Estimated Prophet has a glitch within the first two minutes which is forgivable due to the monster space jam that ensues.

I've said it before, and I am sure I'll say it again All the 90's Dead naysayers (this being post Brent and Bruce), give this Eyes>Estimated>Comes A Time a listen. Unless you have pre-conditioned your brain to not like this era of Dead, I think you will have a difficult time saying this show didn't RAWK!

NICE SET LISTS Good show overall, except the encore of course. While I love the breakouts of Comes a time and casey jones, The ole boy's voice isn't what it use to be, maybe that's why these tunes were never fully brought bacjk in the rotation. but that's anyone's guess. If you are looking for a good 93, this is a best bet

Spring 93' This is a great show not just for 93 but period.
A 9 song first set. Peggy-o and Cassidy were standouts and Casy Jones was the Highlight for me. Eyes-Estimated kicks of a hot second set. The Comes A Time is excellent Probably the best of the Three or 4 they played in the 90's. Garcias solo was powerful and His licks at the end are sick and it ends smoothly nice segue into a very hot Corrinia. Post Drums are pretty average. Wpould have prefered a better encore.
As far a the sound its a little to flat it just doesnt capture the excitement of the venue. Healy really fell off

clipping in days is a high hat dumb ass...give it a closer listen...i even remember thinking billy was laying it on a little heavy that night...certainly one of the best of the modern gd shows...gosh, i loved days...sure, i'm bias because this was "my" era, the 1990s was my first full tour experience...went east for the first time in 92, did everthing i could after the amazing, tears streaming down my face stella from shoreline summer 1992...i miss that...nobody does that for me anymore, especially after the loss of zero then phish...
aw, but i hold out for it to happen again

excellent! great show for the "after brent" years. This was one of my favorite places to see the dead and I always love to see "comes a time". Corrina sucks but thank bobby for no eternity. also thanks to jonathan for giving yet another gem of a digitally flawless recording. no hiss whatsoever. thank you! 4 stars for the show and 50 for the recording!

Billyboy Definitely Billy's high-hat on Days Between.  I do think we are hearing aspects of it that maybe we shouldn't, and he's not 100% in time with the foot over there- The drums are a little hot in the mix and picking up those highs that ought to be hidden a bit more. We're hearing the mechanical attributes of the gear and not just the cymbals on the high hat perhaps.  The danger of soundboards...  you never know what the mix is gonna be like.

This was a great show.  My second to last time seeing Jerry.  The new songs along with Casey and IFTL were a major treat.  This version of Days Between makes up for the fact it never made it onto an album.  My favorite version that I've actually heard.

Still not a 5-star recording.  It is a bit flat at times, but that's probably what was going on for the house sound.  They don't mix at the board for the tapers after all...  And that was probably a good thing.

the Knick the energy level @ the Knick was always incredible. was lucky enough to catch 8 shows there starting w/ the first (check out 3/24/90) & the energy never failed to amaze me. Loose Lucy & casey jones are definitely the highlights of this night. I know a lot of people will disagree w/ me, but I always loved I Fought the Law going back to when I was a kid & Mom used to play the original version. When the Dead started playing it I was happy as hell!!!! As always a great tribute to the original inc. drums for the six gun part. All around great show in a so-so year for the Dead w/ many ups & downs

My favorite venue! It was extremely hard getting tickets for Albany shows. We were denied mailorder so we had to drive to Kingston, NY about a 3 hour drive from my NJ home to the nearest ticketmaster. When you arrived they gave you a ticket number and were told to stand in line. We waited for about an hour and a half. They made an announcement, 20 people were to recieve tickets, too bad there were 500 people online. My friend was one of the lucky ones and I went to both nights. Score!!!!  Albany shows were the shit. The city shut down are Knickerbocker and heads overwhelmed everything. One huge party. This show was not as good as the next night. I found the performance to be a bit uninspired, unenergetic and bit sloppy, maybe its just me. Even a bad Dead show was still a blast and one of the best anyone could spend ones time.

3/5 performance
4/5 sound
5/5 venue and crowd energy

90s haters, repent and listen! I don't understand why people so quickly dismiss the 90s. Yes, 1994 and 1995 were rather poor years. However, they were still playing some great shows through 1993! This is no 5/27/93, but this show once again proves that the boys could still melt faces well into the 90s. The boys show real energy throughout most of the show. Jerry lays down some remarkable solos, and the band tightly jams throughout.

Excellent versions of Estimated, Cassidy, and a top ten Queen Jane for sure. Sound is great. Only weak moments are Jerry's singing, Broken Arrow, and the post space section. Solid 4 stars.

1993 has got to be the most underrated year of the Grateful Dead.

Albania!!!!!!!! "Casey Jones you better drop your speed" The Knick was great. Anybody remember Pagliucci's across the street. TH (Hey Garquia, I think I got on a few stops before you. Last verse "drop your speed". I can spell also. Dumbass.

lobster 12 what are you? Stuck in the 80s Of course they are not going to sound as young as they used to. Great show and a great time.Apparently Lobster has seen 3000 shows. Hmmmmmmmmmmm Maybe his reviews are more diverse but i must say the 90s were not bad. The Gratefully different evolved older Dead of the 90s is the last stage in an epic story of the best jam band ever. They were great in every era. Take a listen make a review let me know what you think.444444444444ssttaarrss

It was a magical night. Huge scene.  Impossible to get a ticket.  Many friends were shut out.  We sat about 10th row right in line with Garcia and man, did this show ever rock.  Incredible first set right from the get go.  Best modern Loose Lucy ever.  Best modern Casey Jones.  Best Queen Jane.  Even the Same Thing had something good to offer.  Second set didn't drop off- Eyes was muscular, Estimated off the charts- listen to the jam in it and Bobby's vocal jam afterwards which wound down nicely into what is as sweet as it comes - Comes A Time.  This one melted me.  And still does.

Post space wasn't spectacular although the Watchtower sure rips and this was the best of all the renditions of IFTL.  By far.

I saw over a 100 shows in the 90's and this was my second favourite behind Giants 91 when they opened with Eyes and wove Dark Star through the whole show.

Listen to this sometime.

It'll put a smile on your face that only love can fill.

peace.

"Drop your spped??? Its casey jones you better watch your speed, not drop your speed. And no that is not a digi noise those are clean high hat cymbals going through the board. What did these people just jump on the bus.
Rainbows End Down That Highway.... Always up for a clean Bobby freak out on Estimated ..with Phil bouncin in the back...woo hoo !

Excellent late era show It was times like this in 1992-93 that would restore my faith in the band and renew my appreciation for them.   All of us who attended shows, in any year, and got to see/hear stuff like this performed in the real were fortunate souls indeed.  The gorgeous sound quality, the energy of the crowd, the funny sideshows that were going on before, during and after and a veggie burrito on the way out...how much better could it get?  I wasn't at THIS show, but it reminds me so much of plenty that I did attend.  The whole performance is wonderful, but I'm especially energized by Jerry's long solo on Bertha...and everyone comps him perfectly (listen to Vince backing him up).  Well, I'm going to finish listening to the rest with particular attention to Broken Arrow and Comes A Time.
What's the tracks after the encore? What show are they from ??? Anybody? Someone? Somebody?!!!!

One of the best of '93 Not just being biased b/c I was there with an awesome floor seat. This is one of the stronger all around post summer '90 shows. First set is about as good as you can hope for from both song selection and performance. Bertha is exceptional, Peggy-O, Broken Arrow, Loose Lucy and Casey Jones all are great! Second set is real good too take out Corina and I Fought The Law and 2nd set is near perfect. Great Eyes and awesome and only Comes of Time of 93 and the only one I ever saw. This is one of the shows I always go back to and love. Can't say that about many post Brent shows..
3 extra songs ... are from 3/17/1993.
